===Etymology===
From {{compound|lang=en|couch|potato}}; coined by Tom Iacino in 1976 as a pun on "boob tuber" ({{m|en|boob tube||television}} and {{m|en|tuber||potato}}); trademarked by Robert Armstrong from 1976–91.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|couch potatoes}}

# A person who [[spend]]s a lot of time [[sitting]] or [[lying]] down, often [[watching]] [[television]], eating [[snack]]s or drinking [[alcohol]].

